ing to understand how your personal information will be treated. The policy may change from time to time so please check back every time you are to use this page or app.<br/><br/><strong>Information in the survey cannot be copied, shared or posted on any mean of communication.</strong><br/><br/><strong> If these Terms and Conditions are not accepted in full, the use of the Poverty Stoplight survey must be terminated immediately.</strong></div>', '0.0.1', '2018', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, 'TC', id FROM ps_network.applications WHERE is_active = TRUE;
INSERT INTO security.termcondpol(id, html, version, year, created_date, type_cod, id_application) SELECT nextval('security.termcondpol_id_seq'), '<html><body><br/><h1>Privacy Policy - Poverty Stoplight Platform</h1><div class="text-box">Please read carefully before using this application.<br/><br/>By entering and using this website you are deemed to accept the provisions in this policy.<br/><br/>This policy applies to all the pages hosted on this site. It does not apply to pages hosted by the Poverty Stoplight’s associates, linked organizations, partners, or to other organizations whose privacy policies may differ.<br/><br/>Please read the following to understand how your personal information will be treated. The policy may change from time to time so please check back every time you are to use this page or app.</div><br/><h4><strong>What information do we collect?</strong></h4><div class="text-box">We collect personal information as volunteered by you when filling out the Poverty Stoplight Survey contained in this page or app. The personal information data includes name, contact information, demographics, socio-economic conditions and current overall status of the quality of life according to the indicators of the Poverty Stoplight methodology.<br/><br/>It is optional to fill out all the fields shown in the survey. In case you wish to delete your response, you will have the option to do so or skip a question you do not want to respond. In case you want to delete all the information you provided, and if you have finished the survey, you also have the option to delete all your previous answers. All information deleted is forever lost, thus it is not stored anywhere in the Poverty Stoplight system.</div><br/><h4><strong>How is your information used?</strong></h4><div class="text-box">The Poverty Stoplight uses the information to inform the organization that administers the survey on the multidimensional life conditions of the people the organization works with, so that it can better address its programs to help improve life-quality indicators that need more attention. The information collected from the survey is also helpful for organizations to monitor and evaluate their impact on the communities where they operate.</div><br/><h4><strong>Does the Poverty Stoplight share your information?</strong></h4><div class="text-box">The information you provide will not be sold or rented nor will it be shared with third parties unless we have your permission or are required to disclose the information by law. It will not disclose information to HMRC, Job Centre, DWP, etc.</div><br/><h4><strong>How secure is the information you give us?</strong></h4><div class="text-box">The Poverty Stoplight Team uses industry standard efforts to safeguard the confidentiality of your personally identifiable information. However, no data transmission over the Internet can be guaranteed to be 100 percent secure, therefore it is not immune to possible attacks by crackers or malicious users who engage in cyber-crime.</div><br/><h4><strong>How can you access, correct or delete your data?</strong></h4><div class="text-box"> You can request the deletion of your information to the representative of the organization that administered the survey to you by email or in person, once you have completed the survey and are not in the presence of that representative within 30 days after you have taken a survey. If you are still in the process of filling out the survey, you have the option of deleting the information you have completed or to skip it.</div><br/><h4><strong>Contact Us</strong></h4><div class="text-box">If you have any questions or suggestions about our Privacy Policy, do not hesitate to contactus.</div></body></html>', '0.0.1', '2018', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, 'PRIV', id FROM ps_network.applications WHERE is_active = TRUE;
